release checklist:
1. Check the output of the test suite
2. Check the output of the example programs
3. Version numbers
3a. Have you set the VERSION string in the Makefile to the new version?
3b. Check if the version number and date are set correctly in the Changes file
3c. Check if the version number is correctly set in the MonoDevelop project
3d. Check if the version number is correctly set in the Doxyfile
3e. Check if the rating prediction and item prediction tools give out the right version numbers
4. Create a copy of the solution file and de-activate the gui parts
5. Check the output of 'git status' - is everything in the repository?
6. Rebuild everything (there should be no warnings)
7. Re-create the API documentation (make apidoc) and visually inspect the results
7a. Check whether the Doxygen output has the correct version number
8. Run 'make release'
9. Packages
9a. Inspect the contents of the source code package from GitHub:
9b. Make a test installation
9c. Inspect the contents of the binary package
9d. Inspect the contents of the documentation package
10. Create the release announcement
11. Add the new version to the website
11a. Copy the --help output of the two command-line tools to the website
12. Commit the website changes
13. Create a git tag: 'git tag -a v2.XX -m "MyMediaLite release 2.XX"'
14. Copy announcement and the packages to the website: 'make copy-website copy-packages-website'
15. Upload the files to GitHub
16. Announce it in the Google Group, on mloss.org, freecode.com, Google+, and Twitter
